@Steve L

On the other hand, I solved this puzzle 8.5% faster than my Monday average.  I honestly didn't see anything that was terribly difficult in it.  But I've been considering that solve times, and the perception of difficulty, for the more experienced may fall differently on a specific puzzle than for the newer solvers for various reasons.  Maybe there's a correlation between a greater bank of knowledge that seems normal to older solvers that isn't really quite as typical to a casual solver.  In this case, knowledge of Latin phrases.  (Noobs: if you don't know ORONO, Maine, or OLLAS, put it in your back pocket; they're going to be back!)

Sometimes, international solvers also have a different experience.  Andrzej said he didn't find this puzzle hard at all.  And Latin phrases hit the same, I guess, in Poland as in the US, while names of US celebrities may not.

